January 15th
is Coming-of-Age day,

931
01:31:52,507 --> 01:31:55,676
an obligatory celebration
in the life of a young Japanese woman.

932
01:31:55,844 --> 01:31:59,847
City governments distribute bags
filled with gifts, date books, advice:

933
01:32:00,515 --> 01:32:03,767
how to be a good citizen,
mother, and wife.

934
01:32:04,728 --> 01:32:08,606
On that day, every 20-year-old girl
can phone her family for free,

935
01:32:08,773 --> 01:32:11,775
no matter where in Japan.

936
01:32:12,485 --> 01:32:16,697
Work, home and country -
this is the anteroom of adulthood.

937
01:32:16,907 --> 01:32:20,910
The world of the Takenoko and of
rock singers speeds away like a rocket.

938
01:32:21,369 --> 01:32:24,955
Speakers explain
what society expects of them.

939
01:32:25,916 --> 01:32:29,251
Ηow long will they take
to forget the secret?

940
01:33:27,894 --> 01:33:30,020
And when
all the celebrations are over,

941
01:33:30,146 --> 01:33:33,857
all that remains is to collect
the ornaments and accessories

942
01:33:33,984 --> 01:33:36,777
and burn them
in one more celebration.

943
01:34:21,698 --> 01:34:23,615
This is dondoyaki,

944
01:34:23,742 --> 01:34:27,828
a Shinto blessing of the debris
that has a right to immortality,

945
01:34:27,954 --> 01:34:29,747
like the dolls at Ueno.

946
01:34:29,914 --> 01:34:33,500
The last stage in the poignancy
of things before they disappear.

947
01:34:34,294 --> 01:34:38,339
Daruma, the one-eyed spirit,
reigns supreme atop the bonfire.

948
01:34:39,257 --> 01:34:42,009
Abandonment must be a feast,
laceration must be a feast,

949
01:34:42,135 --> 01:34:44,595
and the farewell to all
that one has lost, broken, used,

950
01:34:44,763 --> 01:34:46,847
must be ennobled by a ceremony.

951
01:34:47,015 --> 01:34:49,767
It's Japan that could fulfill
the wish of that French writer

952
01:34:49,934 --> 01:34:52,353
who wanted divorce
to be made a sacrament.

953
01:34:52,520 --> 01:34:54,480
The only baffling part of this ritual

954
01:34:54,606 --> 01:34:58,400
was the children striking
the ground with long poles.

955
01:34:58,526 --> 01:35:01,403
I only got one explanation,
a rather peculiar one.

956
01:35:01,529 --> 01:35:04,448
I thought it might be
a small, intimate ritual,

957
01:35:04,574 --> 01:35:07,159
but it was to chase away moles.

958
01:35:49,327 --> 01:35:52,454
And that's where
my three children from Iceland

959
01:35:52,580 --> 01:35:54,581
came and grafted themselves in.

960
01:35:55,458 --> 01:35:57,876
I picked up the whole shot again,

961
01:35:58,002 --> 01:35:59,920
adding the somewhat
hazy ending,

962
01:36:00,088 --> 01:36:03,465
the frame trembling
under the force of the wind.

963
01:36:03,591 --> 01:36:05,676
Everything I had cut
in order to "tidy up"

964
01:36:05,844 --> 01:36:08,887
and that said better than all the rest
what I saw in that moment,

965
01:36:09,055 --> 01:36:11,557
why I held it at arm's length,
at zoom's length,

966
01:36:11,724 --> 01:36:14,768
until its last 24th of a second.

967
01:36:16,438 --> 01:36:19,022
The city of Heimaey
spread out below us,

968
01:36:19,149 --> 01:36:21,275
and when, five years later,
my friend Haroun Tazieff

969
01:36:21,443 --> 01:36:23,694
sent me the film
he'd just shot in the same place,

970
01:36:23,862 --> 01:36:28,782
I lacked only the name to know
that nature performs its own dondoyaki.

971
01:36:29,826 --> 01:36:32,453
The island's volcano had reawakened.

972
01:36:32,787 --> 01:36:34,746
I looked at those pictures,

973
01:36:34,914 --> 01:36:38,959
and it was as if all of 1965
had just been covered in ash.

974
01:36:56,060 --> 01:36:58,061
So all one had to do was wait,

975
01:36:58,229 --> 01:37:01,899
and the planet itself
would stage the working of time.

976
01:37:02,650 --> 01:37:05,694
I saw again
what had been my window.

977
01:37:05,820 --> 01:37:08,655
I saw familiar roofs
and balconies emerge,

978
01:37:08,823 --> 01:37:11,742
the landmarks of the walks
I took through town every day,

979
01:37:11,910 --> 01:37:14,828
down to the cliff
where I'd met the children.

980
01:37:16,039 --> 01:37:20,042
The cat with white socks
that Haroun had kindly filmed for me

981
01:37:20,168 --> 01:37:22,711
naturally found its place,

982
01:37:22,837 --> 01:37:26,465
and I thought that of all the prayers
to time that I'd studied this trip,

983
01:37:26,633 --> 01:37:29,343
the kindest was the one spoken
by the woman of Gotokuji,

984
01:37:29,511 --> 01:37:31,845
who said simply to her cat Tora,

985
01:37:31,971 --> 01:37:36,266
"Beloved cat, wherever you are,
may your soul rest in peace."

986
01:37:58,831 --> 01:38:01,208
And then, in its turn,
the journey entered the Zone.

987
01:38:02,627 --> 01:38:06,547
Hayao showed me my images
already touched by the moss of time,

988
01:38:06,714 --> 01:38:09,675
freed of the lie that had prolonged
the existence of those moments

989
01:38:09,801 --> 01:38:11,510
swallowed by the spiral.

990
01:38:27,944 --> 01:38:30,153
When spring came

991
01:38:30,280 --> 01:38:34,199
and every crow announced its arrival
by raising his cry half a tone...

992
01:38:34,909 --> 01:38:39,788
I took the green train of the Yamanote
line and got off at Tokyo station,

993
01:38:39,914 --> 01:38:42,791
near the central post office.

994
01:38:42,917 --> 01:38:45,168
Though the street was empty,

995
01:38:45,295 --> 01:38:48,046
I waited at the red light,
Japanese-style,

996
01:38:48,172 --> 01:38:51,341
to leave space
for the spirits of broken cars.

997
01:38:51,467 --> 01:38:53,594
Though I was expecting no letter,

998
01:38:53,720 --> 01:38:56,471
I stopped
at the general delivery window,

999
01:38:56,598 --> 01:38:59,391
for one must honor
the spirits of torn-up letters,

1000
01:38:59,517 --> 01:39:04,104
and at the airmail counter,
to hail the spirits of unmailed letters.

1001
01:39:05,148 --> 01:39:07,482
I took the measure
of the unbearable vanity of the West

1002
01:39:07,609 --> 01:39:09,693
that has always favored
being over non-being,

1003
01:39:09,819 --> 01:39:11,653
what is spoken
over what's left unsaid.

1004
01:39:11,779 --> 01:39:15,741
I walked along the little stalls
of clothing dealers.

1005
01:39:15,867 --> 01:39:19,244
In the distance I heard Mr. Akao's voice
reverberating from the loudspeakers,

1006
01:39:19,370 --> 01:39:21,622
now a half tone higher.

1007
01:39:21,789 --> 01:39:24,291
Then I went down to the basement

1008
01:39:24,459 --> 01:39:27,502
where my maniac friend busies
himself with his electronic graffiti.

1009
01:39:27,629 --> 01:39:29,630
In the end
his language touches me,

1010
01:39:29,756 --> 01:39:34,301
for he talks to that part of us that insists
on drawing profiles on prison walls.

1011
01:39:34,427 --> 01:39:36,345
A piece of chalk
to follow the contours

1012
01:39:36,471 --> 01:39:40,140
of what is not,
or is no longer, or is not yet.

1013
01:39:40,391 --> 01:39:43,226
The handwriting each of us
will use to draw up

1014
01:39:43,353 --> 01:39:46,146
his own list of things
that quicken the heart -

1015
01:39:46,272 --> 01:39:49,191
to offer up or to erase.

1016
01:39:49,400 --> 01:39:51,902
In that moment,
poetry will be made by everyone,

1017
01:39:52,028 --> 01:39:54,821
and there will be emus in the Zone."

1018
01:40:14,634 --> 01:40:16,802
He writes to me from Japan.

1019
01:40:16,928 --> 01:40:18,762
He writes to me from Africa.

1020
01:40:18,888 --> 01:40:22,933
He says he can now summon up the look
on the market lady's face in Praia

1021
01:40:23,059 --> 01:40:25,352
that had lasted
only the length of a film frame.

1022
01:40:26,854 --> 01:40:29,690
Will there be
a last letter someday?

